FBIS4-23961 "drafr118_b_94003" FBIS-AFR-94-118 Daily Report 19 Jun 1994 EAST AFRICA Somalia AP Journalist Kidnapped in Mogadishu AP Journalist Kidnapped in Mogadishu LD2006093894 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1609 GMT 19 Jun 94 LD2006093894 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext Italian BFN [Text] Tina Susman, who works for the AP news agency, has been kidnapped in Mogadishu. She was in a four-wheel-drive vehicle, with a police escort, when she was stopped by a group of men who forced her to get out of her vehicle and enter another car. According to investigators, she was kidnapped for a ransom. The police think she was kidnapped by the crew of a car she had rented, and who were then fired because she was about to leave. She managed to contact some people and said she was being treated all right.
